[Anecdotal evidence suggests that sporadic cases of infection with
_Cyclospora cayetanensis_ are seen in Europe. This is the first larger
outbreak reported from Europe, and the data suggest that the source of
infection should be found inside Europe. Infection with _Cyclospora_ is
confirmed if stools are investigated with the modified Ziehl-Neelsen
staining used for identification of _Cryptosporidia_. - Mod.EP
